    "docHtml": "<p>A heavy crossbow quarrel with a thick hardwood shaft and a long, square-section iron spike set deep into a reinforced socket. The heavy bodkin is forged for armor-breaking work — loosed from a windlass-spanned arbalest at close range, it will split the rings of a mail byrnie or dent a breastplate. Garrison crossbowmen and siege troops issue them sparingly, since forging the long spike is exacting work.</p>\n",
